# Odoo Context Parameters

Context is a dictionary passed with every operation containing metadata and instructions.

## Standard Context Keys

### User/Session
- uid - Current user ID
- lang - Language code (en_US, id_ID, etc.)
- tz - Timezone (Asia/Jakarta, UTC, etc.)
- allowed_company_ids - List of company IDs user can access

### Active Record
- active_id - ID of current record
- active_ids - List of selected record IDs
- active_model - Current model name

### Behavior Modifiers
- default_<field> - Set default value for field
- search_default_<filter> - Activate search filter
- group_by - Default grouping
- create - Enable/disable create (True/False)
- edit - Enable/disable edit
- delete - Enable/disable delete

## Common Usage Examples

### Set default values on create
{
  "context": {
    "default_partner_id": 42,
    "default_date_order": "2024-01-15"
  }
}

### Force specific company
{
  "context": {
    "allowed_company_ids": [1],
    "force_company": 1
  }
}

### Skip certain validations
{
  "context": {
    "tracking_disable": true,
    "mail_create_nosubscribe": true,
    "mail_auto_subscribe_no_notify": true
  }
}

### Import mode (skip computed fields)
{
  "context": {
    "import_compat": true
  }
}

## Passing Context in API Calls
For odoo_execute, pass context in kwargs:
{
  "model": "sale.order",
  "method": "action_confirm",
  "args": [[order_id]],
  "kwargs": {
    "context": {"skip_sms": true}
  }
}
